# Accepted-risk findings. Each entry needs a justification and a recheck trigger.

# esbuild dev-server SSRF + install-time integrity issues. esbuild ships only as
# a frontend devDependency (via vite); it never runs in production — the frontend
# is served as a static build behind nginx. Revisit when bumping vite past v5.
GHSA-67mh-4wv8-2f99
GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr

# c-ares in the nginx-unprivileged:alpine base image; fixed in alpine
# (1.34.8-r0) but the upstream image hasn't rebuilt yet. nginx serves static
# files only — no resolver exposure to user input. Remove once the base image
# ships the fixed package (next Dependabot docker PR or manual rebuild).
# 2026-07-11: no longer flagged by the vuln DB despite c-ares 1.34.6-r0 still
# installed — possibly withdrawn upstream, recheck before removing.
CVE-2026-33630

# undici bundled inside the npm CLI's own node_modules in node:20-alpine.
# npm is not executed in the running container (CMD is plain node); the
# vulnerable code path is never loaded. Remove when the node:20-alpine image
# ships an npm with undici >= 6.27.0.
# 2026-07-11: npm is now deleted from the final backend image; entry kept only
# until the branch is merged and confirmed green, then safe to drop.
CVE-2026-12151

# libcrypto3/libssl3 3.5.6-r0 in the node:20-alpine base; 3.5.7-r0 is released
# in alpine but the upstream node image hasn't rebuilt with it yet. Remove on
# the next node:20-alpine digest bump (Dependabot docker PR) — recheck then.
CVE-2026-45447
